(132, 'Notes from @Aakash: Overall: Maybe+ EO: 6-7 | FMF: 5-6 | Thesis: 6 | Price: ? Spikey: ~1 (need refs) - Thesis is a compelling one + have built early momentum - Can see a strong growth mindset and they are building in a deep familiarity space - Would likely have to be a services + product play ideally – for which they seem like an incomplete team - Not SaaS native Next Steps: Push them on GTM thinking with Kuldeep, Rohit and other SaaS folks. Notes Asad Abrar - Drizz.dev Born in Patna Raised by Mother , father used to work in Saudi (used to come once in 2 years) IT KGP 5 years | Order of merit in technology | graduated in 2014 After college got off campus placement @ Baker Hughes 1 year worked at Baker Hughes Then started a company similar to go mechanic Why did you start then ? Had nothing to lose. Was seeing value creation in startups from batch mates Manager at baker hughes was co-founder at the first venture | total 4 co-fos “ You seem like tech inclined how come an ops heavy biz?” That time tech enabled cos we’re all around. Tech to streamlines believer Ran for 1.5 years there | got to monhly 10L GMV Realised problem was two fold : - Old cars for repair used to turn up ..only post service centre cycle was done for the owner - Repair at doorstep was becoming a challenge in an asset light model - Logisitcs of getting parts to doorstep became a challenge - Pivoted to b2b | they were partners for Ola - Realised its a very linear scaling biz and momentum was low - There were a...'),
